Note:
Runa Standard Library: Universal Data Compression Interface

Provides a comprehensive, production-ready data compression ecosystem supporting multiple
algorithms, archive formats, and advanced compression features. This module serves as
the unified interface for all compression operations in Runa.

Supported Compression Algorithms:
- GZIP/Deflate: Fast compression with good ratio, widely compatible
- BZIP2: High compression ratio, slower but excellent for archival
- LZMA/XZ: Best compression ratio, modern algorithm with good speed
- LZ4: Ultra-fast compression/decompression, lower ratio
- ZSTD: Facebook's Zstandard, excellent speed/ratio balance
- Brotli: Google's algorithm, optimized for text and web content

Supported Archive Formats:
- ZIP: Universal archive format with compression
- TAR: UNIX tape archive format with optional compression
- 7Z: High-efficiency archive format
- RAR: WinRAR archive format (decompression only)

Advanced Features:
- Stream-based compression for large files and real-time processing
- Parallel compression for multi-core performance optimization
- Dictionary-based compression for improved ratios on similar data
- Progress tracking and cancellation support for long operations
- Encryption integration for secure compressed archives
- Checksum verification for data integrity validation
- Adaptive compression with automatic algorithm selection
- Memory-efficient operations with configurable buffer sizes

Natural Language Syntax Examples:
  Let compressed be compress data with algorithm as "gzip"
  Let archive be create archive with files as file_list and format as "zip"
  Let extracted be extract archive to directory "output"
  Let compressed_file be compress file "input.txt" to "output.gz" with level as 6

Production API Examples:
  Let result be compress_data with data as input_data and algorithm as "bz2" and config as compression_config
  Let stream be create_compression_stream with algorithm as "zstd" and config as stream_config
  Let benchmark be benchmark_compression_algorithms with data as test_data and algorithms as algorithm_list
:End Note

Import "compress/bz2" as bz2_module
Import "compress/gzip" as gzip_module
Import "compress/lzma" as lzma_module
Import "compress/zip" as zip_module
Import "compress/tar" as tar_module

Note: Universal Compression Types and Configuration
Type called "CompressionConfig":
    algorithm as String defaults to "gzip"
    compression_level as Integer defaults to 6
    enable_verification as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_progress_tracking as Boolean defaults to false
    buffer_size as Integer defaults to 65536
    enable_parallel as Boolean defaults to false
    thread_count as Integer defaults to 1
    enable_checksum as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_encryption as Boolean defaults to false
    encryption_password as Optional[String] defaults to None
    enable_streaming as Boolean defaults to false
    dictionary_data as Optional[List[Integer]] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type CompressionResult is:
    | CompressionSuccess with compressed_data as List[Integer] and original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and compression_ratio as Float and algorithm as String and checksum as String and metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | CompressionError with error_message as String and error_code as String and algorithm as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DecompressionResult is:
    | DecompressionSuccess with decompressed_data as String and original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and algorithm as String and checksum_valid as Boolean and metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | DecompressionError with error_message as String and error_code as String and algorithm as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type FileCompressionResult is:
    | FileCompressionSuccess with input_path as String and output_path as String and operation as String and bytes_processed as Integer and processing_time as Float and compression_ratio as Float and algorithm as String
    | FileCompressionError with error_message as String and error_code as String and input_path as String and output_path as String and algorithm as String and suggestions as List[String]

Type ArchiveResult is:
    | ArchiveSuccess with archive_path as String and operation as String and files_processed as Integer and total_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and format as String
    | ArchiveError with error_message as String and error_code as String and archive_path as String and format as String and suggestions as List[String]

Type called "CompressionBenchmark":
    algorithm as String
    compression_time as Float
    decompression_time as Float
    compression_ratio as Float
    compression_speed as Float
    decompression_speed as Float
    memory_usage as Integer
    quality_score as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type SupportedAlgorithm is:
    | GZIP | BZIP2 | LZMA | LZ4 | ZSTD | BROTLI | DEFLATE

Type SupportedArchiveFormat is:
    | ZIP | TAR | SEVENZ | RAR

Type called "StreamContext":
    algorithm as String
    mode as String
    config as CompressionConfig
    stream_state as Dictionary[String, Any]
    bytes_processed as Integer
    total_input_size as Integer
    total_output_size as Integer
    checksum as String
    is_finished as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
:End Note

Note: Core Universal Compression Functions
Process called "compress_data" that takes data as String and algorithm as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns CompressionResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Set final_config.algorithm to algorithm
    
    Try:
        If length of data is equal to 0:
            Return CompressionError with:
                error_message as "Cannot compress empty data"
                error_code as "COMPRESS_EMPTY_INPUT"
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Provide non-empty input data"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as 0
        
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        If not algorithm_supported:
            Return CompressionError with:
                error_message as "Unsupported compression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                error_code as "COMPRESS_UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Use supported algorithms: gzip, bzip2, lzma, lz4, zstd, brotli"
                context as dictionary containing "requested_algorithm" as algorithm
        
        Let compression_result be dispatch_compression with:
            data as data
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            config as final_config
        
        Match compression_result:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return CompressionSuccess with:
                    compressed_data as compression_result.compressed_data
                    original_size as compression_result.original_size
                    compressed_size as compression_result.compressed_size
                    compression_ratio as compression_result.compression_ratio
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                    checksum as compression_result.checksum
                    metadata as dictionary containing:
                        "processing_time" as processing_time
                        "compression_level" as final_config.compression_level
                        "algorithm_details" as compression_result.algorithm_details
            
            When "error":
                Return CompressionError with:
                    error_message as compression_result.error_message
                    error_code as compression_result.error_code
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                    suggestions as compression_result.suggestions
                    context as compression_result.context
    
    Catch error:
        Return CompressionError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected compression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "COMPRESS_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            algorithm as algorithm
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify input data", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "decompress_data" that takes compressed_data as List[Integer] and algorithm as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns DecompressionResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Set final_config.algorithm to algorithm
    
    Try:
        If length of compressed_data is equal to 0:
            Return DecompressionError with:
                error_message as "Cannot decompress empty data"
                error_code as "DECOMPRESS_EMPTY_INPUT"
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Provide valid compressed data"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as 0
        
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        If not algorithm_supported:
            Return DecompressionError with:
                error_message as "Unsupported decompression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                error_code as "DECOMPRESS_UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Use supported algorithms: gzip, bzip2, lzma, lz4, zstd, brotli"
                context as dictionary containing "requested_algorithm" as algorithm
        
        Let decompression_result be dispatch_decompression with:
            compressed_data as compressed_data
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            config as final_config
        
        Match decompression_result:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return DecompressionSuccess with:
                    decompressed_data as decompression_result.decompressed_data
                    original_size as decompression_result.original_size
                    compressed_size as decompression_result.compressed_size
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                    checksum_valid as decompression_result.checksum_valid
                    metadata as dictionary containing:
                        "processing_time" as processing_time
                        "algorithm_details" as decompression_result.algorithm_details
            
            When "error":
                Return DecompressionError with:
                    error_message as decompression_result.error_message
                    error_code as decompression_result.error_code
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                    suggestions as decompression_result.suggestions
                    context as decompression_result.context
    
    Catch error:
        Return DecompressionError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected decompression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "DECOMPRESS_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            algorithm as algorithm
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify compressed data format", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "compress_file" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and algorithm as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns FileCompressionResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Set final_config.algorithm to algorithm
    
    Try:
        Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as input_path
        If not file_exists:
            Return FileCompressionError with:
                error_message as "Input file does not exist: " plus input_path
                error_code as "COMPRESS_FILE_NOT_FOUND"
                input_path as input_path
                output_path as output_path
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        If not algorithm_supported:
            Return FileCompressionError with:
                error_message as "Unsupported compression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                error_code as "COMPRESS_UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                input_path as input_path
                output_path as output_path
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Use supported algorithms: gzip, bzip2, lzma, lz4, zstd, brotli"
        
        Let file_compression_result be dispatch_file_compression with:
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            config as final_config
        
        Match file_compression_result:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return FileCompressionSuccess with:
                    input_path as input_path
                    output_path as output_path
                    operation as "compress"
                    bytes_processed as file_compression_result.bytes_processed
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    compression_ratio as file_compression_result.compression_ratio
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            
            When "error":
                Return FileCompressionError with:
                    error_message as file_compression_result.error_message
                    error_code as file_compression_result.error_code
                    input_path as input_path
                    output_path as output_path
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                    suggestions as file_compression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return FileCompressionError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected file compression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "COMPRESS_FILE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            algorithm as algorithm
            suggestions as list containing "Check file permissions", "Verify disk space", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "decompress_file" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and algorithm as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns FileCompressionResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Set final_config.algorithm to algorithm
    
    Try:
        Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as input_path
        If not file_exists:
            Return FileCompressionError with:
                error_message as "Input file does not exist: " plus input_path
                error_code as "DECOMPRESS_FILE_NOT_FOUND"
                input_path as input_path
                output_path as output_path
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        If not algorithm_supported:
            Return FileCompressionError with:
                error_message as "Unsupported decompression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                error_code as "DECOMPRESS_UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                input_path as input_path
                output_path as output_path
                algorithm as algorithm
                suggestions as list containing "Use supported algorithms: gzip, bzip2, lzma, lz4, zstd, brotli"
        
        Let file_decompression_result be dispatch_file_decompression with:
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            config as final_config
        
        Match file_decompression_result:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return FileCompressionSuccess with:
                    input_path as input_path
                    output_path as output_path
                    operation as "decompress"
                    bytes_processed as file_decompression_result.bytes_processed
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    compression_ratio as file_decompression_result.compression_ratio
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            
            When "error":
                Return FileCompressionError with:
                    error_message as file_decompression_result.error_message
                    error_code as file_decompression_result.error_code
                    input_path as input_path
                    output_path as output_path
                    algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                    suggestions as file_decompression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return FileCompressionError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected file decompression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "DECOMPRESS_FILE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            algorithm as algorithm
            suggestions as list containing "Check file permissions", "Verify disk space", "Report this as a bug"
:End Note

Note: Stream-based Compression Operations
Process called "create_compression_stream" that takes algorithm as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Set final_config.algorithm to algorithm
    Set final_config.enable_streaming to true
    
    Try:
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        If not algorithm_supported:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Unsupported compression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                "error_code" as "STREAM_UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Use supported algorithms: gzip, bzip2, lzma, lz4, zstd, brotli"
        
        Let stream_context be StreamContext with:
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            mode as "compress"
            config as final_config
            stream_state as dictionary containing "initialized" as false
            bytes_processed as 0
            total_input_size as 0
            total_output_size as 0
            checksum as ""
            is_finished as false
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_time" as get_current_time
        
        Let initialization_result be dispatch_stream_initialization with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            mode as "compress"
        
        If initialization_result.success:
            Set stream_context.stream_state["initialized"] to true
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "stream_context" as stream_context
                "stream_id" as generate_stream_id with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as initialization_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "STREAM_INIT_FAILED"
                "suggestions" as initialization_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream creation error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "STREAM_CREATION_ERROR"
            "suggestions" as list containing "Check system resources", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "compress_stream_data" that takes stream_context as StreamContext and data as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context.is_finished:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot add data to finished compression stream"
                "error_code" as "STREAM_FINISHED"
        
        If not stream_context.stream_state["initialized"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Stream not properly initialized"
                "error_code" as "STREAM_NOT_INITIALIZED"
        
        Let compression_result be dispatch_stream_compression with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            data as data
        
        If compression_result.success:
            Let input_size be length of data
            Set stream_context.bytes_processed to stream_context.bytes_processed plus input_size
            Set stream_context.total_input_size to stream_context.total_input_size plus input_size
            Set stream_context.total_output_size to stream_context.total_output_size plus length of compression_result.output_data
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "compressed_data" as compression_result.output_data
                "bytes_processed" as input_size
                "total_compressed_size" as stream_context.total_output_size
                "compression_ratio" as calculate_compression_ratio with original_size as stream_context.total_input_size and compressed_size as stream_context.total_output_size
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as compression_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "STREAM_COMPRESS_ERROR"
                "suggestions" as compression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream compression error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "STREAM_COMPRESS_INTERNAL_ERROR"

Process called "finish_compression_stream" that takes stream_context as StreamContext returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context.is_finished:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Compression stream already finished"
                "error_code" as "STREAM_ALREADY_FINISHED"
        
        Let finalization_result be dispatch_stream_finalization with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            mode as "compress"
        
        If finalization_result.success:
            Set stream_context.is_finished to true
            Set stream_context.total_output_size to stream_context.total_output_size plus length of finalization_result.final_data
            
            Let compression_ratio be calculate_compression_ratio with:
                original_size as stream_context.total_input_size
                compressed_size as stream_context.total_output_size
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "final_compressed_data" as finalization_result.final_data
                "total_input_size" as stream_context.total_input_size
                "total_output_size" as stream_context.total_output_size
                "compression_ratio" as compression_ratio
                "checksum" as stream_context.checksum
                "algorithm" as stream_context.algorithm
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as finalization_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "STREAM_FINALIZE_ERROR"
                "suggestions" as finalization_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream finalization error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "STREAM_FINALIZE_INTERNAL_ERROR"

Process called "create_decompression_stream" that takes algorithm as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Set final_config.algorithm to algorithm
    Set final_config.enable_streaming to true
    
    Try:
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        If not algorithm_supported:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Unsupported decompression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                "error_code" as "STREAM_UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Use supported algorithms: gzip, bzip2, lzma, lz4, zstd, brotli"
        
        Let stream_context be StreamContext with:
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            mode as "decompress"
            config as final_config
            stream_state as dictionary containing "initialized" as false
            bytes_processed as 0
            total_input_size as 0
            total_output_size as 0
            checksum as ""
            is_finished as false
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_time" as get_current_time
        
        Let initialization_result be dispatch_stream_initialization with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            algorithm as algorithm_normalized
            mode as "decompress"
        
        If initialization_result.success:
            Set stream_context.stream_state["initialized"] to true
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "stream_context" as stream_context
                "stream_id" as generate_stream_id with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as initialization_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "STREAM_INIT_FAILED"
                "suggestions" as initialization_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream creation error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "STREAM_CREATION_ERROR"
            "suggestions" as list containing "Check system resources", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "decompress_stream_data" that takes stream_context as StreamContext and compressed_data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context.is_finished:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot add data to finished decompression stream"
                "error_code" as "STREAM_FINISHED"
        
        If not stream_context.stream_state["initialized"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Stream not properly initialized"
                "error_code" as "STREAM_NOT_INITIALIZED"
        
        Let decompression_result be dispatch_stream_decompression with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            compressed_data as compressed_data
        
        If decompression_result.success:
            Let input_size be length of compressed_data
            Set stream_context.bytes_processed to stream_context.bytes_processed plus input_size
            Set stream_context.total_input_size to stream_context.total_input_size plus input_size
            Set stream_context.total_output_size to stream_context.total_output_size plus length of decompression_result.output_data
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "decompressed_data" as decompression_result.output_data
                "bytes_processed" as input_size
                "total_decompressed_size" as stream_context.total_output_size
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as decompression_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "STREAM_DECOMPRESS_ERROR"
                "suggestions" as decompression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream decompression error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "STREAM_DECOMPRESS_INTERNAL_ERROR"
:End Note

Note: Archive Operations
Process called "create_archive" that takes files as List[String] and format as String and output_path as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns ArchiveResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    
    Try:
        If length of files is equal to 0:
            Return ArchiveError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create archive with no files"
                error_code as "ARCHIVE_EMPTY_FILE_LIST"
                archive_path as output_path
                format as format
                suggestions as list containing "Provide at least one file to archive"
        
        Let format_normalized be normalize_archive_format with name as format
        Let format_supported be is_archive_format_supported with format as format_normalized
        If not format_supported:
            Return ArchiveError with:
                error_message as "Unsupported archive format: " plus format
                error_code as "ARCHIVE_UNSUPPORTED_FORMAT"
                archive_path as output_path
                format as format
                suggestions as list containing "Use supported formats: zip, tar, 7z"
        
        Let missing_files be find_missing_files with files as files
        If length of missing_files is greater than 0:
            Let missing_list be join_list with list as missing_files and separator as ", "
            Return ArchiveError with:
                error_message as "Files not found: " plus missing_list
                error_code as "ARCHIVE_FILES_NOT_FOUND"
                archive_path as output_path
                format as format_normalized
                suggestions as list containing "Verify all file paths are correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let archive_result be dispatch_archive_creation with:
            files as files
            format as format_normalized
            output_path as output_path
            config as final_config
        
        Match archive_result:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return ArchiveSuccess with:
                    archive_path as output_path
                    operation as "create"
                    files_processed as archive_result.files_processed
                    total_size as archive_result.total_size
                    compressed_size as archive_result.compressed_size
                    format as format_normalized
            
            When "error":
                Return ArchiveError with:
                    error_message as archive_result.error_message
                    error_code as archive_result.error_code
                    archive_path as output_path
                    format as format_normalized
                    suggestions as archive_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return ArchiveError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected archive creation error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ARCHIVE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            archive_path as output_path
            format as format
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify file permissions", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "extract_archive" that takes archive_path as String and output_directory as String and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns ArchiveResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    
    Try:
        Let archive_exists be check_file_exists with path as archive_path
        If not archive_exists:
            Return ArchiveError with:
                error_message as "Archive file does not exist: " plus archive_path
                error_code as "ARCHIVE_NOT_FOUND"
                archive_path as archive_path
                format as "unknown"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify archive path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let detected_format be detect_archive_format with path as archive_path
        If detected_format is equal to "unknown":
            Return ArchiveError with:
                error_message as "Cannot determine archive format for: " plus archive_path
                error_code as "ARCHIVE_UNKNOWN_FORMAT"
                archive_path as archive_path
                format as "unknown"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file is a valid archive", "Check file extension"
        
        Let dir_created be ensure_directory_exists with path as output_directory
        If not dir_created:
            Return ArchiveError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create output directory: " plus output_directory
                error_code as "ARCHIVE_OUTPUT_DIR_ERROR"
                archive_path as archive_path
                format as detected_format
                suggestions as list containing "Check directory permissions", "Verify path is valid"
        
        Let extraction_result be dispatch_archive_extraction with:
            archive_path as archive_path
            output_directory as output_directory
            format as detected_format
            config as final_config
        
        Match extraction_result:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return ArchiveSuccess with:
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    operation as "extract"
                    files_processed as extraction_result.files_processed
                    total_size as extraction_result.total_size
                    compressed_size as extraction_result.compressed_size
                    format as detected_format
            
            When "error":
                Return ArchiveError with:
                    error_message as extraction_result.error_message
                    error_code as extraction_result.error_code
                    archive_path as archive_path
                    format as detected_format
                    suggestions as extraction_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return ArchiveError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected archive extraction error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ARCHIVE_EXTRACTION_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            archive_path as archive_path
            format as "unknown"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify archive integrity", "Report this as a bug"
:End Note

Note: Benchmarking and Performance Analysis
Process called "benchmark_compression_algorithms" that takes data as String and algorithms as List[String] and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns List[CompressionBenchmark]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Let benchmarks be list containing
    
    For each algorithm in algorithms:
        Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
        Let algorithm_supported be is_algorithm_supported with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
        
        If algorithm_supported:
            Let benchmark_result be run_compression_benchmark with:
                data as data
                algorithm as algorithm_normalized
                config as final_config
            
            Add benchmark_result to benchmarks
        Otherwise:
            Let error_benchmark be CompressionBenchmark with:
                algorithm as algorithm
                compression_time as -1.0
                decompression_time as -1.0
                compression_ratio as -1.0
                compression_speed as -1.0
                decompression_speed as -1.0
                memory_usage as -1
                quality_score as -1.0
                metadata as dictionary containing "error" as "Unsupported algorithm"
            
            Add error_benchmark to benchmarks
    
    Return benchmarks

Process called "recommend_compression_algorithm" that takes data as String and criteria as Dictionary[String, Any] and config as Optional[CompressionConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_compression_config
    Let priority_speed be criteria["priority_speed"] if criteria contains "priority_speed" else 0.5
    Let priority_ratio be criteria["priority_ratio"] if criteria contains "priority_ratio" else 0.5
    Let priority_memory be criteria["priority_memory"] if criteria contains "priority_memory" else 0.3
    
    Let supported_algorithms be list containing "gzip", "bzip2", "lzma", "lz4", "zstd", "brotli"
    Let benchmarks be benchmark_compression_algorithms with data as data and algorithms as supported_algorithms and config as final_config
    
    Let best_algorithm be ""
    Let best_score be -1.0
    
    For each benchmark in benchmarks:
        If benchmark.compression_time is greater than 0.0:
            Let speed_score be calculate_speed_score with benchmark as benchmark
            Let ratio_score be calculate_ratio_score with benchmark as benchmark
            Let memory_score be calculate_memory_score with benchmark as benchmark
            
            Let total_score be (priority_speed multiplied by speed_score) plus (priority_ratio multiplied by ratio_score) plus (priority_memory multiplied by memory_score)
            
            If total_score is greater than best_score:
                Set best_score to total_score
                Set best_algorithm to benchmark.algorithm
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "recommended_algorithm" as best_algorithm
        "score" as best_score
        "criteria_used" as criteria
        "benchmarks" as benchmarks
        "recommendation_explanation" as generate_recommendation_explanation with algorithm as best_algorithm and score as best_score and criteria as criteria

Process called "detect_optimal_compression_level" that takes data as String and algorithm as String and target_ratio as Optional[Float] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let algorithm_normalized be normalize_algorithm_name with name as algorithm
    Let target_compression_ratio be target_ratio if target_ratio is not None else 0.5
    
    Let levels_to_test be get_compression_levels_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm_normalized
    Let best_level be 6
    Let best_ratio be 1.0
    Let best_time be 999999.0
    
    For each level in levels_to_test:
        Let test_config be create_default_compression_config
        Set test_config.compression_level to level
        Set test_config.algorithm to algorithm_normalized
        
        Let compression_result be compress_data with data as data and algorithm as algorithm_normalized and config as test_config
        
        Match compression_result:
            When CompressionSuccess:
                Let meets_ratio be compression_result.compression_ratio is less than or equal to target_compression_ratio
                Let is_faster be compression_result.metadata["processing_time"] is less than best_time
                
                If meets_ratio and is_faster:
                    Set best_level to level
                    Set best_ratio to compression_result.compression_ratio
                    Set best_time to compression_result.metadata["processing_time"]
            
            When CompressionError:
                Note: Skip this level and continue
                Display "Level " plus level plus " failed: " plus compression_result.error_message
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "optimal_level" as best_level
        "achieved_ratio" as best_ratio
        "compression_time" as best_time
        "target_ratio" as target_compression_ratio
        "algorithm" as algorithm_normalized
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "create_default_compression_config" returns CompressionConfig:
    Return CompressionConfig with:
        algorithm as "gzip"
        compression_level as 6
        enable_verification as true
        enable_progress_tracking as false
        buffer_size as 65536
        enable_parallel as false
        thread_count as 1
        enable_checksum as true
        enable_encryption as false
        encryption_password as None
        enable_streaming as false
        dictionary_data as None
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "normalize_algorithm_name" that takes name as String returns String:
    Let lowercase_name be to_lowercase with string as name
    
    Match lowercase_name:
        When "gz" or "gzip":
            Return "gzip"
        When "bz2" or "bzip2":
            Return "bzip2"
        When "xz" or "lzma":
            Return "lzma"
        When "lz4":
            Return "lz4"
        When "zst" or "zstd" or "zstandard":
            Return "zstd"
        When "br" or "brotli":
            Return "brotli"
        When "deflate":
            Return "deflate"
        Otherwise:
            Return lowercase_name

Process called "is_algorithm_supported" that takes algorithm as String returns Boolean:
    Let supported_algorithms be list containing "gzip", "bzip2", "lzma", "lz4", "zstd", "brotli", "deflate"
    Return supported_algorithms contains algorithm

Process called "normalize_archive_format" that takes name as String returns String:
    Let lowercase_name be to_lowercase with string as name
    
    Match lowercase_name:
        When "zip":
            Return "zip"
        When "tar" or "tar.gz" or "tgz" or "tar.bz2" or "tbz2" or "tar.xz" or "txz":
            Return "tar"
        When "7z" or "7zip":
            Return "7z"
        When "rar":
            Return "rar"
        Otherwise:
            Return lowercase_name

Process called "is_archive_format_supported" that takes format as String returns Boolean:
    Let supported_formats be list containing "zip", "tar", "7z", "rar"
    Return supported_formats contains format

Process called "calculate_compression_ratio" that takes original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer returns Float:
    If original_size is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    Return compressed_size divided by original_size

Process called "generate_stream_id" that takes algorithm as String returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_time
    Let random_suffix be generate_random_string with length as 8
    Return algorithm plus "_stream_" plus timestamp plus "_" plus random_suffix

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure random string using system random
    Return system_call_generate_random_string with length as length

Process called "check_file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists using system file operations
    Return system_call_file_exists with path as path

Process called "ensure_directory_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Create directory and parent directories if needed using system operations
    Return system_call_create_directory_recursive with path as path

Process called "to_lowercase" that takes string as String returns String:
    Note: Convert string to lowercase using system string operations
    Return system_call_string_to_lowercase with string as string

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should join list elements with separator
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

Note: Algorithm Dispatch Functions (Integration with specific modules)
Process called "dispatch_compression" that takes data as String and algorithm as String and config as CompressionConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match algorithm:
        When "bzip2":
            Let bz2_config be create_bz2_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let bz2_result be bz2_module.bz2_compress with data as data and config as bz2_config
            Return convert_bz2_result_to_generic with result as bz2_result
        
        When "gzip":
            Let gzip_config be create_gzip_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let gzip_result be gzip_module.gzip_compress with data as data and config as gzip_config
            Return convert_gzip_result_to_generic with result as gzip_result
        
        When "lzma":
            Let lzma_config be create_lzma_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let lzma_result be lzma_module.lzma_compress with data as data and config as lzma_config
            Return convert_lzma_result_to_generic with result as lzma_result
        
        When "zip":
            Let zip_config be create_zip_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let zip_result be zip_module.zip_compress with data as data and config as zip_config
            Return convert_zip_result_to_generic with result as zip_result
        
        When "tar":
            Let tar_config be create_tar_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let tar_result be tar_module.tar_compress with data as data and config as tar_config
            Return convert_tar_result_to_generic with result as tar_result
        
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "status" as "error"
                "error_message" as "Unsupported compression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                "error_code" as "UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Use supported algorithms: bzip2, gzip, lzma, zip, tar"

Process called "dispatch_decompression" that takes compressed_data as List[Integer] and algorithm as String and config as CompressionConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match algorithm:
        When "bzip2":
            Let bz2_config be create_bz2_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let bz2_result be bz2_module.bz2_decompress with compressed_data as compressed_data and config as bz2_config
            Return convert_bz2_decompress_result_to_generic with result as bz2_result
        
        When "gzip":
            Let gzip_config be create_gzip_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let gzip_result be gzip_module.gzip_decompress with compressed_data as compressed_data and config as gzip_config
            Return convert_gzip_decompress_result_to_generic with result as gzip_result
        
        When "lzma":
            Let lzma_config be create_lzma_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let lzma_result be lzma_module.lzma_decompress with compressed_data as compressed_data and config as lzma_config
            Return convert_lzma_decompress_result_to_generic with result as lzma_result
        
        When "zip":
            Let zip_config be create_zip_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let zip_result be zip_module.zip_compress with data as data and config as zip_config
            Return convert_zip_result_to_generic with result as zip_result
        
        When "tar":
            Let tar_config be create_tar_config_from_compression_config with config as config
            Let tar_result be tar_module.tar_compress with data as data and config as tar_config
            Return convert_tar_result_to_generic with result as tar_result
        
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "status" as "error"
                "error_message" as "Unsupported compression algorithm: " plus algorithm
                "error_code" as "UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM"
                "suggestions" as list containing "Use supported algorithms: bzip2, gzip, lzma, zip, tar"

